The paper deals with unsupervised feature learning in computer vision using deep convolutional neural networks (ConvNets). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques for feature learning, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper proposes a novel approach for unsupervised feature learning, which involves predicting image rotations, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves neural networks, which makes cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques for evaluating the performance of the proposed approach, which makes cs.CL (Computation and Language) another possible sub-category.
